        "action": "Pause further UK North Sea Oil and Gas Decommissioning Until 2040.",
        "additional_details": "OIL is and will remain necessary for 60m tonnes per year European plastics industry. Fuel extraction currently supports 320 000 UK jobs.Oil import supply/price is vulnerable to global instability.\r\nsources:\r\nhttp://www.thenational.scot/news/16059661.north-sea-set-for-oil-boom-as-estimates-are-increased-by-billions-of-barrels/\r\nhttps://oilandgasuk.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Workforce-Report-2017-Oil-Gas-UK.pdf\r\nhttps://www.statista.com/statistics/282732/global-production-of-plastics-since-1950/",
        "background": "The UK has already met and exceeded its EU 2030 co2 emissions reduction target of  40% reduction on 1990 levels.\r\nThere are 11.7bn barrels oil in existing  UK wells, worth \u00a3724.581Bn.\r\nIt is irrational to pay $80 per barrel to import a resource that we have. Decommissioning should be paused til 2040",
